sentences: In 1946–47, some record sessions for the new label Dial were organized in Hollywood, with Charlie Parker and McGhee.
The first was held on July 29, 1946.
Drug problems sidelined McGhee for much of the 1950s, but he resurfaced in the 1960s, appearing in many George Wein productions.
His career sputtered again in the mid-1960s and he did not record again until 1976.
He taught music through the 1970s, both in classrooms and at his apartment in midtown Manhattan and instructed musicians like Charlie Rouse in music theory.
McGhee died on July 17, 1987 at the age of 69, a memorial service was held for him on July 24, 1987.

sentences: Howard McGhee (March 6, 1918 – July 17, 1987) was one of the first American bebop jazz trumpeters, with Dizzy Gillespie, Fats Navarro and Idrees Sulieman.
Around this time, McGhee was a leading musician in the Los Angeles bebop scene, participating in many concerts, recording, and even managing a night club for a period.
Drug problems sidelined McGhee for much of the 1950s, but he resurfaced in the 1960s, appearing in many George Wein productions.
